132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1576
H.P. 1034 House of Representatives, April 10, 2025
An Act to Extend a One-year Lobbying Prohibition to Partisan and
Nonpartisan Staff of the Legislature
Reference to the Committee on Veterans and Legal Affairs suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative RIELLY of Westbrook.
Cosponsored by Senator BENNETT of Oxford and
Representatives: ANKELES of Brunswick, BOYER of Poland, CARLOW of Buxton, FROST
of Belgrade, GRAHAM of North Yarmouth, HYMES of Waldo, SUPICA of Bangor, Senator:
HICKMAN of Kennebec.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 3 MRSA §318-B, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 337, §2, is amended by
3 amending the section headnote to read:
4 §318-B. Former executive branch or legislative branch employee lobbying prohibited
5 Sec. 2. 3 MRSA §318-B, sub-§1, ¶C, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 337, §2, is repealed
6 and the following enacted in its place:
7 C. "Former employee from the executive branch or legislative branch" means:
8 (1) An employee who was employed in the executive branch of this State:
9 (a) In the unclassified service, as defined in Title 5, section 7032, subsection
10 6‑A;
11 (b) In the classified service;
12 (c) In a position for which the salary is subject to adjustment by the Governor
13 under Title 2, section 6; or
14 (d) In a major policy-influencing position under Title 5, chapter 71; and
15 (2) An employee who was employed in the Legislature, including a partisan
16 legislative employee, nonpartisan legislative employee, committee clerk or
17 employee of the Office of the Secretary of the Senate or the Clerk of the House.
18 Sec. 3. 3 MRSA §318-B, sub-§2, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 337, §2, is repealed
19 and the following enacted in its place:
20 2. Lobbying prohibited. Beginning January 1, 2026, a former officer or former
21 employee from the executive branch or legislative branch may not engage in compensated
22 lobbying until one year after the termination of the employee's executive branch or
23 legislative branch employment.
24 Sec. 4. Effective date. This Act takes effect January 1, 2026.
25 SUMMARY
2266 Under current law, former executive branch employees are prohibited from lobbying
2277 until one year after the termination of their employment in the executive branch. This bill
2288 extends the one-year prohibition on lobbying to include former employees of the legislative
2299 branch, beginning January 1, 2026.
